# No Exposed API URLs

Never hardcode API base URLs, endpoints, or service URLs in the codebase. Always use environment variables so that URLs can be configured per environment (dev, staging, prod) and remain out of version control when they are sensitive.

## Guidelines

- Use environment variables (e.g. `VITE_API_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`, `API_BASE_URL`) for all API base URLs
- Store defaults only in `.env.example` or similar template files, never in committed `.env`
- Never commit `.env` files that contain real URLs

## Examples

```javascript
// ❌ BAD
const API_URL = 'https://api.example.com/v1';
fetch('https://api.example.com/v1/users');

// ✅ GOOD
const API_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL ?? process.env.API_URL;
fetch(`${API_URL}/users`);
```

```javascript
// ❌ BAD
const endpoint = 'https://staging.api.myapp.com/data';

// ✅ GOOD
const endpoint = `${process.env.REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL}/data`;
```
